SIMPLE: foregoer
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Foregoer
<hw>Fore*go"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
goes before another; a predecessor; hence, an ancestor; a
progenitor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A purveyor of the king; -- so called, formerly, from
<xex>going before</xex> to provide for his household.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Foregoer</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Foregoer
<hw>Fore*go"er</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Etymologically
<ets>forgoer</ets>.]</ety> <def>One who forbears to enjoy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>foregone</ent>⟦br⟧
